trend_summary: Built-up cover rose modestly: infill blocks and parking garages replaced open lots, while the airport gained a larger terminal, aprons and taxiways. Highway interchanges were re-aligned and widened. Riverbank landscaping added tree cover. Despite growth, the area retains a medium-density, transport-oriented suburban character.
notable_changes: New terminal, aprons and extra taxiways enlarge the airport on the southeast side.
Mid-rise office/residential blocks constructed on former parking or vacant lots in the central district.
Surface parking near the large five-sided complex converted to multi-level garages.
Major highway and bridge approaches re-configured and widened, especially on the northeast edge.
Riverfront greenway expanded with additional tree planting and landscaped open space.
